(59, 'Lead Based Heat Stabilizers', 'lead-based-heat-stabilizers', 'Leading PVC heat stabilizers manufacturers & supplier India', 'Buy PVC heat stabilizers from leading world-class manufactures at the most affordable rates, we are a certified suppliers & exporter of stabilizers in India.', '<script type=\"application/ld+json\">\r\n	{\r\n	  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\r\n	  \"@type\": \"FAQPage\",\r\n	  \"mainEntity\": [{\r\n		\"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n		\"name\": \"What are the benefits of using One pack PVC Heat Stabilizers?\",\r\n		\"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n		  \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n		  \"text\": \"<p>There are several benefits of using our one pack PVC Heat Stabilizers that include: reduced labour cost, reduced handling losses, reduced inventory, a better homogenous mixture from processing. We provide PVC Heat Stabilizers (one pack- lead-based) in powder and flakes form, that can be modified as per the needs and requirements of the customers.</p> \"\r\n		}\r\n	  },{\r\n		\"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n		\"name\": \"What is the preferred dosage of PVC Heat Stabilizers?\",\r\n		\"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n		  \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n		  \"text\": \"<p>The dosage of stabilizers per hundred parts of resin ( PVC ) is 2.5-3.5 phr in pipes and 3.0 to 12.0 phr in different types of cables, but it depends on lead content in stabilizer and the filler used by PVC product manufacturer. If the filler is more, the dosage required is more. Detailed application knowledge and formula/recipe for any customer can be provided by our technical services managers.</p> \"\r\n		}\r\n	  },{\r\n		\"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n		\"name\": \"Why should I purchase PVC Heat Stabilizers From MLA Group?\",\r\n		\"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n		  \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n		  \"text\": \"<p>At MLA Group, we manufacture products under a controlled environment and with high precision, strict quality controls, and standardized procedures to bring you a premium product every single time. Due to our huge capacity and aggressive approach, our prices are most economical. We are a <b> leading PVC heat stabilizers suppliers in India </b> who is committed to continuous improvement through R&D, to serve the customers with quality products at lower costs through higher productivity and unmatched customer service.</p> \"\r\n	\r\n		}\r\n	  }]\r\n	}\r\n	</script>', 'product-image/unistab.webp', '', '23', 'Unpublished', '<h2>Leading PVC heat stabilizers manufacturers in India</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group Of Industries is a&nbsp;<strong>leading PVC heat stabilizer manufacturers in India</strong>, involved in the production of PVC heat stabilizers of premium quality.Starting from a single reactor the company now has grown multi-fold to be the leading PVC Stabilizer manufacturer in India. The company has a production capacity of 3000 tons per month. One of the key players in the PVC additives industry, we have been the preferred&nbsp;<strong>PVC heat stabilizer suppliers in the world</strong>, supplying high performance stabilizers to a large number of PVC manufacturing companies across the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are committed to providing our customers best quality products at competitive prices. With fast and reliable supplies, we have grown into the most reliable brand in the industry, established trust based relations with leading PVC processors worldwide, and have become a&nbsp;<strong>leading PVC heat stabilizers suppliers and exporters in the world</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Product - Pvc Heat Stabilizers</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We provide PVC Heat Stabilizers (one packs - lead based &amp; calcium-zinc non-toxic) in powder and flakes form. In PVC Processing (extrusion, injection molding, etc.), the polymer is subjected to a high temperature which can lead to burning (degradation or breaking of polymer chains). Heat stabilizers are lead compounds that are added to prevent burning by capturing and inactivating the labile chlorine that is produced on heating of PVC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conventionally, a combination of three chemicals, TBLS, DBLS, and LS (Tribasic lead sulphate, dibasic Lead stearate, and Lead stearate) were used as heat stabilizers along with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/calcium-stearate-manufacturers.html\">Calcium Stearate&nbsp;</a>as a co-stabilizer. MLA Group is the leading manufacture of these&nbsp;<strong>single stabilizers</strong>&nbsp;in the highest purity and performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nowadays, one&ndash;pack stabilizer is used in place of the three chemicals as a heat stabilizer. It is made by in-situ reaction of lead oxide with stearic acid along with many other components like waxes, antioxidants, inorganic stabilizers etc, which were not there in the conventional system of single stabilizers above.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its performance depends on two things:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>the lead oxide content which provides stabilization by deactivating the chloride radical formed during heated melt processing of PVC during extrusion and</li>\r\n	<li>by providing lubrication so that the residence time inside the screw extruder (heated zone) is reduced, so less deterioration is there.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group produces a dozen of popular one-pack grades with different lead contents as well as over a hundred customized grades.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why Choose Us as Your Pvc Heat Stabilizers Suppliers in India</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group of Industries has been a leading name as&nbsp;<strong>PVC heat stabilizer manufacturers in the world</strong>, known for providing products that are backed by a superior quality guarantee and that conform to international standards. We have a fully-equipped, in-house laboratory with trained and experienced specialists who work with customers to develop products as per specific needs and requirements. Our PVC laboratory has a two roll mixing mill, a Rheometer, moulding press for making sheet, Congo red tester, VR/ IR tester, a pilot extrusion line etc. The application lab helps us in developing value added products and providing technical support to our customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are a company that thrives on providing technical support to cater the customer needs. We make sure that our products pass a series of quality control checks before they reach our customers. Our stringent quality checks procedures are inspected regularly in order to maintain the highest international standards. Our R&amp;D constantly strives hard to produce only the best quality products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For decades, We are known to be the leading PVC Stabilizers manufacturers in India. We currently serve more than 200 companies and export to over 46 countries around every corner of the globe worldwide, constantly growing, making us a&nbsp;<strong>leading PVC heat stabilizers exporters in India and the world</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>FAQS</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What Are the Benefits of Using One Pack Pvc Heat Stabilizers?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are several benefits of using our one pack PVC Heat Stabilizers that include: reduced labour cost, reduced handling losses, reduced inventory, a better homogenous mixture from processing. We provide PVC Heat Stabilizers (one pack- lead-based) in powder and flakes form, that can be modified as per the needs and requirements of the customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is the Preferred Dosage of Pvc Heat Stabilizers?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The dosage of stabilizers per hundred parts of resin ( PVC ) is 2.5-3.5 phr in pipes and 3.0 to 12.0 phr in different types of cables, but it depends on lead content in stabilizer and the filler used by PVC product manufacturer. If the filler is more, the dosage required is more. Detailed application knowledge and formula/recipe for any customer can be provided by our technical services managers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why Should I Purchase Pvc Heat Stabilizers From Mla Group?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>At MLA Group, we manufacture products under a controlled environment and with high precision, strict quality controls, and standardized procedures to bring you a premium product every single time. Due to our huge capacity and aggressive approach, our prices are most economical. We are a&nbsp;<strong>leading PVC heat stabilizers suppliers in India&nbsp;</strong>who is committed to continuous improvement through R&amp;D, to serve the customers with quality products at lower costs through higher productivity and unmatched customer service.</p>\r\n', '', '<h3>Applications</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Tribasic lead sulphate, Dibasic lead stearate, Lead stearate are used as heat stabilizers while processing PVC items so that they do not get burnt/degraded due to high temperatures used in processing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our one packs are a combination of above and other additives such as anti-oxidants etc., all put together in one product which provides ease of handling while its function is the same as above: to provide heat stability to PVC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At MLA Group, we have developed a full range of PVC Stabilizers to be used in various industries with different applications that include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PVC Rigid Pipes &amp; Conduits,</li>\r\n	<li>PVC Fittings,</li>\r\n	<li>PVC Wires and Cables,</li>\r\n	<li>PVC Floor covering,</li>\r\n	<li>PVC Soil Pipes for gases and liquids.</li>\r\n	<li>Other products such as shoe compounds, suction hoses, gasket sheets, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2024-04-25 07:39:07', '2024-11-06 10:37:56'),
(60, 'Zinc Stearate', 'zinc-stearate-manufacturers', 'Leading Zinc Stearate manufacturers & suppliers in India', 'The company is the leading manufacturer in India of Zinc Stearate and has a supreme quality product with safe supply and export facilities throughout the world.', '<script type=\"application/ld+json\">\r\n	{\r\n	  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\r\n	  \"@type\": \"FAQPage\",\r\n	  \"mainEntity\": [{\r\n		\"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n		\"name\": \"Is zinc stearate a dangerous product?\",\r\n		\"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n		  \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n		  \"text\": \"<p><b>Zinc stearate manufacturers</b> supply premium quality zinc stearate that is often used in the plastics processing industry as an environmentally friendly heat stabilizer, so, it is not a dangerous product. It is widely used, but the operation process must be carried out in strict accordance with the operating regulations to achieve good results and avoid unnecessary troubles and losses. </p> \"\r\n		}\r\n	  },{\r\n		\"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n		\"name\": \"What precautions should I take while storing zinc stearate? \",\r\n		\"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n		  \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n		  \"text\": \"<p>Store zinc stearate in a cool and ventilated warehouse. Keep away from fire and heat sources. It should be stored separately from oxidants and acids, and avoid mixed storage, equipped with the appropriate variety and quantity of fire equipment. The storage area should be equipped with suitable materials to contain the leakage. </p> \"\r\n		}\r\n	  },{\r\n		\"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n		\"name\": \"Why should I choose MLA Group as my Zinc Stearate suppliers?\",\r\n		\"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n		  \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n		  \"text\": \"<p>If you want standard-quality products from one of the leading<b> Zinc Stearate exporters in the world</b>, at fair market prices you should definitely consider us as your <b>Zinc Stearate suppliers</b>. Our company adheres to strict quality controls and conducts quality inspections in accordance with the prescribed standards to ensure that the product pass rate meets our customer needs.</p>\"\r\n	\r\n		}\r\n	  }]\r\n	}\r\n	</script>', 'product-image/ZN STR.webp', '', '17', 'Unpublished', '<p>MLA Group of industries is one of the&nbsp;<strong>leading Zinc Stearate manufacturers in India</strong>, known for providing application specific grades with excellent peformance at fair market prices. We make UNIFLOW range of zinc stearate by fusion, precipitation and our proprietory semi-wet process. Our enterprise integrates R&amp;D, production, and sales, backed by a team of professionals, all of whom are experienced engineers in this industry. We continue to make advancements in our production equipment and production technology to keep up with our image as a leading global player and one of the top&nbsp;<strong>Zinc Stearate suppliers in India.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have strict controls on the raw materials and use imported raw materials where needed to ensure the stability of the quality of the finished products. Our company has a complete inspection laboratory for raw materials and finished products, which guarantees a 100% pass rate of the products shipped. The quality control is organized in a three-tier process- the shopfloor lab, the factory quality control and the central quality control.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The Product - Zinc Stearate</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Zinc stearate is a &quot;zinc soap&quot; that is widely used in a number of industrial processes. We mostly follow the semi-wet production process which combines the characteristics of high purity, transparency, and good thermal stability. At the same time, it has been tested and used in the petrochemical industry to prove that the product quality indicators are equal to or better than similar imported products. It is an environmentally friendly heat stabilizer and lubricant for the processing of plastic raw materials, plastic masterbatches, engineering plastics, and rubber compounds.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Zinc Stearate Properties</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>White fine powder.</li>\r\n	<li>Melting point: 118-125&deg;C.</li>\r\n	<li>Relative density: 1.095.</li>\r\n	<li>Insoluble in water, soluble in organic solvents such as hot ethanol, benzene, toluene, and turpentine.</li>\r\n	<li>After heating and dissolving in an organic solvent, it becomes a jelly when cooled.</li>\r\n	<li>Decomposes with strong acid.</li>\r\n	<li>It has a fire hazard under dry conditions, with a spontaneous ignition point of 900&deg;C, and a tendency to absorb moisture.</li>\r\n	<li>Non-toxic and can be used for products in contact with food</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Uses of Zinc Stearate</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group, a&nbsp;<strong>leading Zinc Stearate manufacturers in the world</strong>, supplies premium quality Zinc stearate that is widely used in several industries such as the pharmaceutical industry, plastics, masterbatches, SMC/ BMC, rubber industry, cosmetics, Petrochemicals resin manufacturing, wood coating industry, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The main uses of zinc stearate are :</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>As a non-toxic stabilizer for polyvinyl chloride</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It can be used as a non-toxic stabilizer for polyvinyl chloride, with low initial coloration and good weather resistance. This product is not easy to use alone, because it has a significant catalytic effect on the degradation of polyvinyl chloride, and after a period of time, the product can change color rapidly. It has a synergistic stabilizing action with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/calcium-stearate-manufacturers.html\">calcium stearate</a>. With barium cadmium soap, it is used for general soft products.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>As a lubricant</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It is vastly used in the masterbatches and filler compounds industry as an internal lubricant, dispersing and release agent. It is also used as a lubricant for styrene resin, including polystyrene, ABS, and SAN resin, and a release agent for transparent products. In the rubber industry, this product can be used as a rubber lubricant and diaphragm agent (anti-sticking). In addition. It can also be used as a textile polishing agent, paint flattening agent, and cosmetic ingredients.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Metal soap powder.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Used in the creation of powder, pressed powder, etc. It is mainly used as an adhesive of fragrance powder to increase the adhesion of fragrance powder on the skin. Zinc stearate is light and soft, and when added to powder cosmetics, it covers the outside of other powders, making the powder easily permeable.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Other Uses</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Anti-foaming agent. Light and heat stabilizer. Paint smoothing agent and abrasive. Drying lubricant and release agent for feet. Stabilizer, release agent, lubricant for plastic products. Waterproofing agent for concrete, brown asbestos, paper, and fabric. Used in cosmetics and ointments.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why Choose Us as Your Zinc Stearate Suppliers?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>At MLA Group, we integrate R&amp;D, production, and sales into one seamless delightful experience for our customers. Relying on new technologies from our in-house R&amp;D and reliable product quality guarantee, backed with application research and technical services, we have created a national high-tech enterprise that is among the top&nbsp;<strong>Zinc Stearate exporters in India</strong>. We are committed to implementing a modern enterprise management system, mainly producing plastic&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/pvc-heat-stabilizers-manufacturers.html\">heat stabilizers</a>&nbsp;and lubricants. We have in-house application labs to check the performance of our product in rubber, plastics and paints and have gone to the extend of installing high speed mixers, two roll mill, moulding, rheometer, extruders and other pilot plants to check for the perfect performance of our product in these applications and continually improve the quality. We also use these labs for providing free technical services to our customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our brand is hailed as a&nbsp;<strong>leading Zinc Stearate exporters in India</strong>&nbsp;and is well received by all our customers. We have amassed several honors as one of the<strong>&nbsp;top Zinc Stearate suppliers</strong>&nbsp;in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UNIFLOW range of zinc stearates has the following unique properties:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Low moisture :</strong>&nbsp;As we use multi-stage dryer which nobody else in India is doing our product is always having less than 1% moisture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Low FFA (free fatty matter) or FFA (free fatty acid):</strong>&nbsp;this is basically the unreacted stearic acid and should be less than 1.5%. In our DLI-TS grade it is lowest, less than 0.5%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Clear Melt :</strong>&nbsp;Our melt is transparent and either white or light yellow in colour. If it is dark colour or non-transparent it shows adulteration or improper processing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Heavy metals and iron:</strong>&nbsp;Our product is free from heavy metals. Normally other manufacturers do not have the technology to completely remover the heavy metals which come from the zinc or calcium salt (raw material). Our product has almost complete removal of such heavy metals and iron.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Electrolytes/Salt :</strong>&nbsp;As our products are washed very carefully on fully automatic filter presses, our salt contents are less than 0.5%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also our plant - reaction vessels, drying equipment etc. are all made of stainless steel SS316L, aluminium and polypropylene due to which there is no iron contamination in our stearates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bulk density also plays a role in many applications. We have a range of bulk densities, which also reflects finer particle size and porosity (higher absorption) in the product.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>FAQs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Is zinc stearate a dangerous product?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Zinc stearate manufacturers</strong>&nbsp;supply premium quality zinc stearate that is often used in the plastics processing industry as an environmentally friendly heat stabilizer, so, it is not a dangerous product. It is widely used, but the operation process must be carried out in strict accordance with the operating regulations to achieve good results and avoid unnecessary troubles and losses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What precautions should I take while storing zinc stearate?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Store zinc stearate in a cool and ventilated warehouse. Keep away from fire and heat sources. It should be stored separately from oxidants and acids, and avoid mixed storage, equipped with the appropriate variety and quantity of fire equipment. The storage area should be equipped with suitable materials to contain the leakage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should I choose MLA Group as my Zinc Stearate suppliers?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want standard-quality products from one of the leading<strong>&nbsp;Zinc Stearate exporters in the world</strong>, at fair market prices you should definitely consider us as your&nbsp;<strong>Zinc Stearate suppliers</strong>. Our company adheres to strict quality controls and conducts quality inspections in accordance with the prescribed standards to ensure that the product pass rate meets our customer needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<h3>Applications</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>As a non-toxic stabilizer for polyvinyl chloride</li>\n	<li>As a lubricant</li>\n	<li>Metal soap powder.</li>\n	<li>Anti-foaming agent.</li>\n	<li>Light and heat stabilizer.</li>\n	<li>Paint smoothing agent and abrasive.</li>\n	<li>Drying lubricant and release agent for feet.</li>\n</ul>\n', '2024-04-25 07:46:43', '2024-11-06 10:38:04'),
