(84, 'Sorbitan Monostearate', 'sorbitan-monostearate-manufacturers-in-india', 'Leading Sorbitan Monosearate Manufacturers in India', 'MLA Group is a leading manufacturer & supplier of Sorbitan Monosearate, we are one of the best exporters of SMS in the world offering the best price.', 'test', 'product-image/sorbitan.jpg', '', '', 'Published', '<h2>Sorbitan Monostearate (SMS)</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group is a leading Sorbitan Monostearate manufacturers in India with over several decades of experience in the chemical industry. Our strong global chemical resource capabilities, professional control quality management system, and unparalleled customer support provide you with high-quality chemical products for industrial production. That&#39;s the reason MLA is a Star Export House with exports to over 50 countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our company follows a stringent 3-tier Quality Control System and FEMA ensuring the safety, consistency, and reliability of our product. Our reputation precedes us making us one of the most sought-after Sorbitan Monostearate manufacturers in the World.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Sorbitan Monostearate - Product Description</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorbitan monostearate is a synthetic ester made by the reaction of Sorbitan with stearic acid under controlled conditions. SMS is used in the manufacture of food and healthcare products as a non-ionic surfactant with emulsifying, dispersing, and wetting properties. It is also employed to create synthetic fibers, metal machining fluid, and as a brightener in the leather industry. It is used in yeast manufacturing to protect the yeast from excess drying and also helps rehydrate the yeast cells.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorbitan monostearate (abbreviation SMS), or Span 60, is an emulsifier esterified from Sorbitan and stearic acid with the European food additive number E491. This ingredient is mostly used in baking yeast by improving the activity of instant dry yeast when the yeast is rehydrated before use.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Appearance and properties</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A white to yellow waxy bead or flake with a slight characteristic smell.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>HYDROPHILIC-LIPOPHILIC BALANCE (HLB)</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>With the HLB value of 4.7, meaning it is lipophilic and soluble in oil instead of water. It will form W/O (water-in-oil) type emulsion, and it is a strong emulsifying dispersion and has a wetting effect. A white to yellow waxy bead or flake with a slight characteristic smell.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>HYDROPHILIC-LIPOPHILIC BALANCE (HLB)</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>With the HLB value of 4.7, meaning it is lipophilic and soluble in oil instead of water. It will form W/O (water-in-oil) type emulsion, and it is a strong emulsifying dispersion and has a wetting effect</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Leading Sorbitan Monostearate suppliers in India</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Our Advantage</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>100% genuine products</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We produce an authentic veg origin high-quality Sorbitan Monostearate. All types of compliances and quality assurance certifications are available.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Prompt responses</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We believe in fast and timely responses and are able to provide you with all the required information in a short period of time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Competitive prices</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>While we provide high-quality Sorbitan Monostearate, we also make sure that we provide the best market prices for our products. This is made possible by our high economies of scale for various esters.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Excellent Customer Support</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We aim to provide the best sales and after-sales services to our customers, backed with technical and commercial support.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Fast and timely delivery</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We have an efficient logistics system in place to look over the delivery of products and also make sure of their safe transit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>FAQs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Answered by the leading Sorbitan Monostearate exporters in India</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Is the Sorbitan Monostearate manufactured by you Halal?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, as the leading Sorbitan Monostearate manufacturers and exporters in the world, we provide a synthetic ester that would be halal complying with the Muslim policy as the fatty acid stearic acid is derived from vegetable oils instead of animal origins.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Is Sorbitan Monostearate manufactured by you Vegan?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, it is vegan as the raw material stearic acid is derived from vegetable oils and the manufacturing process is without the use of animal matter or products derived from animal origin.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the shelf life of Sorbitan Monostearate manufactured by you? Also, what is the legal status on the same?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Shelf Life:</strong>&nbsp;Sorbitan Monostearate manufactured at MLA Group has a shelf life of one year from the date of production, if stored under mentioned storage conditions and unopened packaging.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Legal Status:</strong>Our SMS meets the specifications fixed by FAO/WHO and the EU. However, users must check for permissibility for the use of this product in foods in their own country as the food laws may differ in each country.</p>\r\n', '', '<h2>Uses of Sorbitan monostearate</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As leading suppliers and exporters of Sorbitan Monostearate in the world, we have been serving many foods and other industries with absolute consistency in quality at a reasonable cost.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Food Applications</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorbitan monostearate or SMS is used as an emulsifier, commonly together with polysorbates to keep water and oil mixed in many food products.<br />\r\nIt is commonly used in instant fat and oil emulsions, desserts, food supplements, cake, spread, margarine, coffee whiteners.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dry yeast: maintain the moisture, increase the shelf life of dry yeast, and help the rehydration of yeast cells before blended with other dough ingredients.</li>\r\n	<li>Ice cream: promote emulsification of dairy fat, prevent the formation of ice crystals, and improve the mouthfeel.</li>\r\n	<li>Margarine: improve emulsion stability and reduce sandiness.</li>\r\n	<li>Whipping cream: improve foam volume and contribute to a nice and stiff foam.</li>\r\n	<li>Bread &amp; Cake: increase the loaf volume and improve the texture of bread and cake.</li>\r\n	<li>Confections and chocolate: stabilize the emulsion of oils and fats.</li>\r\n	<li>Flavored fermented milk products.</li>\r\n	<li>Beverage whiteners.</li>\r\n	<li>Fat and oil emulsions.</li>\r\n	<li>Sugar confectionery.</li>\r\n	<li>Chewing gum.</li>\r\n	<li>Decorations, coatings, and fillings.</li>\r\n	<li>Fine bakery wares.</li>\r\n	<li>Emulsified sauces.</li>\r\n	<li>Desserts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Non-food applications</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pharmaceuticals &amp; Cosmetics</li>\r\n	<li>Plastic food wrap</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2024-09-27 13:59:16', '2024-09-27 14:01:25'),
(85, 'Leading PVC heat stabilizers manufacturers & supplier India', 'pvc-heat-stabilizers-manufacturer', 'Leading PVC heat stabilizers manufacturers & supplier India', 'Buy PVC heat stabilizers from leading world-class manufactures at the most affordable rates, we are a certified suppliers & exporter of stabilizers in India.', 'code', 'product-image/heat.jpg', '', '', 'Unpublished', '<p>MLA Group Of Industries is a&nbsp;<strong>leading PVC heat stabilizer manufacturers in India</strong>, involved in the production of PVC heat stabilizers of premium quality.Starting from a single reactor the company now has grown multi-fold to be the leading PVC Stabilizer manufacturer in India. The company has a production capacity of 3000 tons per month. One of the key players in the PVC additives industry, we have been the preferred&nbsp;<strong>PVC heat stabilizer suppliers in the world</strong>, supplying high performance stabilizers to a large number of PVC manufacturing companies across the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are committed to providing our customers best quality products at competitive prices. With fast and reliable supplies, we have grown into the most reliable brand in the industry, established trust based relations with leading PVC processors worldwide, and have become a&nbsp;<strong>leading PVC heat stabilizers suppliers and exporters in the world</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Product - PVC Heat Stabilizers</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We provide PVC Heat Stabilizers (one packs - lead based &amp; calcium-zinc non-toxic) in powder and flakes form. In PVC Processing (extrusion, injection molding, etc.), the polymer is subjected to a high temperature which can lead to burning (degradation or breaking of polymer chains). Heat stabilizers are lead compounds that are added to prevent burning by capturing and inactivating the labile chlorine that is produced on heating of PVC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conventionally, a combination of three chemicals, TBLS, DBLS, and LS (Tribasic lead sulphate, dibasic Lead stearate, and Lead stearate) were used as heat stabilizers along with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/calcium-stearate-manufacturers.html\">Calcium Stearate&nbsp;</a>as a co-stabilizer. MLA Group is the leading manufacture of these&nbsp;<strong>single stabilizers</strong>&nbsp;in the highest purity and performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nowadays, one&ndash;pack stabilizer is used in place of the three chemicals as a heat stabilizer. It is made by in-situ reaction of lead oxide with stearic acid along with many other components like waxes, antioxidants, inorganic stabilizers etc, which were not there in the conventional system of single stabilizers above.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its performance depends on two things:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;the lead oxide content which provides stabilization by deactivating the chloride radical formed during heated melt processing of PVC during extrusion and</li>\r\n	<li>by providing lubrication so that the residence time inside the screw extruder (heated zone) is reduced, so less deterioration is there.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group produces a dozen of popular one-pack grades with different lead contents as well as over a hundred customized grades.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why Choose Us as Your PVC Heat Stabilizers Suppliers In India</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group of Industries has been a leading name as&nbsp;<strong>PVC heat stabilizer manufacturers in the world</strong>, known for providing products that are backed by a superior quality guarantee and that conform to international standards. We have a fully-equipped, in-house laboratory with trained and experienced specialists who work with customers to develop products as per specific needs and requirements. Our PVC laboratory has a two roll mixing mill, a Rheometer, moulding press for making sheet, Congo red tester, VR/ IR tester, a pilot extrusion line etc. The application lab helps us in developing value added products and providing technical support to our customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are a company that thrives on providing technical support to cater the customer needs. We make sure that our products pass a series of quality control checks before they reach our customers. Our stringent quality checks procedures are inspected regularly in order to maintain the highest international standards. Our R&amp;D constantly strives hard to produce only the best quality products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For decades, We are known to be the leading PVC Stabilizers manufacturers in India. We currently serve more than 200 companies and export to over 46 countries around every corner of the globe worldwide, constantly growing, making us a&nbsp;<strong>leading PVC heat stabilizers exporters in India and the world</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>FAQs</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the benefits of using One pack PVC Heat Stabilizers?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There are several benefits of using our one pack PVC Heat Stabilizers that include: reduced labour cost, reduced handling losses, reduced inventory, a better homogenous mixture from processing. We provide PVC Heat Stabilizers (one pack- lead-based) in powder and flakes form, that can be modified as per the needs and requirements of the customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the preferred dosage of PVC Heat Stabilizers?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The dosage of stabilizers per hundred parts of resin ( PVC ) is 2.5-3.5 phr in pipes and 3.0 to 12.0 phr in different types of cables, but it depends on lead content in stabilizer and the filler used by PVC product manufacturer. If the filler is more, the dosage required is more. Detailed application knowledge and formula/recipe for any customer can be provided by our technical services managers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why should I purchase PVC Heat Stabilizers From MLA Group?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>At MLA Group, we manufacture products under a controlled environment and with high precision, strict quality controls, and standardized procedures to bring you a premium product every single time. Due to our huge capacity and aggressive approach, our prices are most economical. We are a&nbsp;<strong>leading PVC heat stabilizers suppliers in India&nbsp;</strong>who is committed to continuous improvement through R&amp;D, to serve the customers with quality products at lower costs through higher productivity and unmatched customer service.</p>\r\n', '', '<h3>APPLICATION OF PVC STABILIZERS</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Tribasic lead sulphate, Dibasic lead stearate, Lead stearate are used as heat stabilizers while processing PVC items so that they do not get burnt/degraded due to high temperatures used in processing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our one packs are a combination of above and other additives such as anti-oxidants etc., all put together in one product which provides ease of handling while its function is the same as above: to provide heat stability to PVC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At MLA Group, we have developed a full range of PVC Stabilizers to be used in various industries with different applications that include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PVC Rigid Pipes &amp; Conduits,</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;PVC Fittings,</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;PVC Wires and Cables,</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;PVC Floor covering,</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;PVC Soil Pipes for gases and liquids.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Other products such as shoe compounds, suction hoses, gasket sheets, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2024-12-02 11:04:26', '2024-12-02 11:07:05');
